00:39:22,455 --> 00:39:23,922
in case something happened,

703
00:39:23,989 --> 00:39:25,923
you know,
life is very capricious.

704
00:39:25,991 --> 00:39:29,586
A stroke, a sudden embolism
or lightning...
You know I...

705
00:39:29,929 --> 00:39:31,954
Darling, I love you.
I mean that sincerely.

706
00:39:32,031 --> 00:39:35,330
You're a wonderful woman,
you're a tremendous servant
and a credit to your race.

707
00:39:35,401 --> 00:39:37,596
And I mean that. From
the bottom of my heart
I say that to you.

708
00:39:37,670 --> 00:39:39,194
I notice you didn't
get the red sweater.

709
00:39:39,271 --> 00:39:40,932
She probably left it
in another bedroom.

710
00:39:41,006 --> 00:39:43,201
You know,
she's got a little problem
with promiscuity.

711
00:39:43,275 --> 00:39:44,435
But...

712
00:39:44,643 --> 00:39:47,874
So, I'll be going.
I'll call you.
We'll have lunch.

713
00:39:56,154 --> 00:40:00,523
Mr. Lyman, sir, Mr. Spence
has been here and he's
been into the music room.

714
00:40:01,292 --> 00:40:02,589
What do you mean?

715
00:40:02,861 --> 00:40:04,852
A most unusual
sequence of events.

716
00:40:04,929 --> 00:40:07,193
Mr. Spence came by
looking for his
daughter's sweater.

717
00:40:07,265 --> 00:40:08,755
Said she'd requested it.

718
00:40:08,833 --> 00:40:11,063
Next thing I knew,
he was in the music room.

719
00:40:11,569 --> 00:40:14,060
Sir, I think
he'd been drinking,
from his behavior.

720
00:40:15,006 --> 00:40:17,304
Yes, yes.

721
00:40:17,909 --> 00:40:20,503
Yes. Okay, Margaret,
thank you. Goodbye.

722
00:40:21,646 --> 00:40:22,806
Is everything okay?

723
00:40:22,881 --> 00:40:25,748
Yes.
Yes, it will be.

724
00:41:40,922 --> 00:41:43,914
It's so nice
to be out here with you,
just away

725
00:41:44,926 --> 00:41:47,360
from the rest of the world
and...
Hmm.

726
00:41:47,429 --> 00:41:51,923
Yes, I often
come out here to read and,
well, and fish.

727
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:53,490
There's trout in the lake.

728
00:42:02,410 --> 00:42:03,934
What are you thinking about?

729
00:42:05,113 --> 00:42:06,705
You really want to know?
Yes.

730
00:42:09,217 --> 00:42:11,879
Just how ironic life is,
and tragic.

731
00:42:12,420 --> 00:42:13,682
Why?

732
00:42:14,256 --> 00:42:16,850
Well, that I met you
by rescuing you from drowning

733
00:42:17,658 --> 00:42:19,489
and found you
totally enchanting

734
00:42:20,628 --> 00:42:24,086
and now we've come full cycle
and, alas, you're going
to have to drown.

735
00:42:27,134 --> 00:42:28,226
What?

736
00:42:28,669 --> 00:42:31,763
Oh, I imagine by now
Sidney's confirmed
that I killed Betty Gibson.

737
00:42:31,839 --> 00:42:34,433
I mean, in my own defense,
there really was
no other way out.

738
00:42:35,476 --> 00:42:37,774
At first I managed
to hide my identity from her,

739
00:42:37,845 --> 00:42:40,006
but I saw her too many times
over the years

740
00:42:41,282 --> 00:42:43,045
and she learned who I was,
and...

741
00:42:43,584 --> 00:42:45,745
Well, it became
a constant demand for money

742
00:42:45,819 --> 00:42:48,049
and I just
could not let that go on,
could I?

743
00:42:49,089 --> 00:42:51,080
I mean, my whole life
and career

744
00:42:51,158 --> 00:42:53,991
would be
just hostage to her
moods at all times.

745
00:42:56,229 --> 00:42:58,459
So, I studied
the Tarot case,

746
00:42:58,531 --> 00:43:00,863
I rehearsed my plan,
and, well, you know the rest.

747
00:43:00,967 --> 00:43:02,867
If you do something to me,
Sidney's gonna find out!

748
00:43:02,936 --> 00:43:04,062
He'll tell someone.

749
00:43:04,137 --> 00:43:06,697
No, no, no.
You see, you will go
in a boating accident,

750
00:43:06,773 --> 00:43:08,468
and Sidney will go
later tonight.

751
00:43:08,908 --> 00:43:11,069
No one knows
of your relationship with him,

752
00:43:11,511 --> 00:43:14,036
because, after all,
you're not actually father
and daughter, are you?

753
00:43:14,781 --> 00:43:17,841
And no one will think twice
to investigate the death
of some obscure vaud...

754
00:43:17,917 --> 00:43:19,145
Are you listening?

755
00:43:19,452 --> 00:43:21,317
No one will think twice
to investigate the death

756
00:43:21,387 --> 00:43:24,948
of some obscure vaudevillian
called Splendini, who is
really a stranger to me.

757
00:43:25,692 --> 00:43:26,716
Help!

758
00:43:26,793 --> 00:43:28,556
Help! Someone help me!

759
00:43:37,502 --> 00:43:39,094
Yes, very quiet, isn't it?

760
00:43:42,407 --> 00:43:44,432
This is the advantage
of a private lake.

761
00:43:48,547 --> 00:43:50,515
Get off me!
Get off me!

762
00:43:52,417 --> 00:43:53,577
Get off me!
Come...

763
00:45:12,929 --> 00:45:14,556
Yes, police.

764
00:45:16,232 --> 00:45:19,633
Yes, this is Peter Lyman.
I need the police immediately.

765
00:45:20,203 --> 00:45:22,193
At the Lyman estate.

766
00:45:22,705 --> 00:45:26,300
There's been
a terrible boating accident.
A woman has drowned.

767
00:45:26,375 --> 00:45:28,070
It's awful.
Please come right away.

768
00:45:28,143 --> 00:45:29,633
Thank you. Thank you.

769
00:45:36,552 --> 00:45:38,247
They think they know
where the body is.

770
00:45:39,455 --> 00:45:40,922
I'm so sorry, sir.

771
00:45:44,093 --> 00:45:45,822
When last I saw her,
she...

772
00:45:49,565 --> 00:45:52,056
She just said she wanted
to go out there to
communicate with nature.

773
00:45:53,602 --> 00:45:55,536
Just to think
she wanted some
peace and quiet and...

774
00:45:55,971 --> 00:45:57,996
She wasn't depressed,
or anything like that,
was she, sir?

775
00:45:58,073 --> 00:45:59,062
God, no. No.

776
00:45:59,407 --> 00:46:01,602
I mean, unless she was
keeping it from me.

777
00:46:01,876 --> 00:46:03,537
You heard no cries for help?

778
00:46:03,611 --> 00:46:07,069
No! No,
I was listening to music
in here, damn it.

779
00:46:07,782 --> 00:46:09,374
It's just so ironic.

780
00:46:09,450 --> 00:46:10,576
Because the way
I first met her

781
00:46:10,651 --> 00:46:12,881
I rescued her
from drowning
in our club pool.

782
00:46:12,954 --> 00:46:15,445
And she was a very,
very weak swimmer.

783
00:46:16,190 --> 00:46:17,350
Hello?

784
00:46:18,626 --> 00:46:21,117
I was faking it at the pool
to get your attention.

785
00:46:21,496 --> 00:46:24,556
Actually, I used to be
captain of the Brooklyn
Community Swim Team.

786
00:46:39,446 --> 00:46:41,004
Fascinating observation.

787
00:46:41,181 --> 00:46:43,775
Lyman lost a cufflink
at the flat of a prostitute,

788
00:46:43,850 --> 00:46:46,318
who was later killed
by the Tarot Card Killer.

789
00:46:47,487 --> 00:46:51,014
Well, this upright chap
certainly enjoyed patronizing
some dodgy women.

790
00:46:51,491 --> 00:46:55,052
Unfortunately
for Elizabeth Gibson,
she elected to blackmail him.

791
00:46:56,429 --> 00:46:58,454
It's a beautifully
written story

792
00:46:58,598 --> 00:47:02,466
and one of the best bits
of investigative journalism
in a long time.

793
00:47:02,836 --> 00:47:04,804
And this paper
is proud to run it.

794
00:47:04,871 --> 00:47:07,271
Oh, I have to
share the credit
with Joe Strombel.

795
00:47:07,574 --> 00:47:08,598
An inspiration,

796
00:47:08,675 --> 00:47:11,041
who taught me more
than I could ever
explain to anyone.

797
00:47:11,111 --> 00:47:13,874
And to the late
Sidney Waterman.

798
00:47:14,613 --> 00:47:15,739
Splendini.

799
00:47:15,881 --> 00:47:18,611
A nice guy who helped out
with the investigation

800
00:47:18,684 --> 00:47:21,312
and without whom
I never could have made it.

801
00:47:22,721 --> 00:47:25,212
Sidney, wherever you are,

802
00:47:26,358 --> 00:47:27,791
I'll never forget you.

803
00:47:30,162 --> 00:47:31,026
How did you get here?

804
00:47:31,430 --> 00:47:32,488
Me?

805
00:47:32,598 --> 00:47:36,295
I couldn't get used to driving
on the goddamn wrong
side of the street!

806
00:47:36,368 --> 00:47:38,359
You know,
I was driving up
to the country,

807
00:47:38,437 --> 00:47:41,372
and in the United States,
I would have been a hero.
I would have saved her.

808
00:47:41,440 --> 00:47:42,429
I would have...

809
00:47:42,508 --> 00:47:45,033
But here, you know...
That's the one drawback
of living in London.

810
00:47:45,110 --> 00:47:48,238
Granted, the theater's better,
there's many good
Indian restaurants.

811
00:47:48,314 --> 00:47:49,508
Well, what did you do?

812
00:47:49,615 --> 00:47:52,174
What do I do?
I'm Splendini. Magician.

813
00:47:53,384 --> 00:47:55,352
Would you like
to see something?
Oh, yes, please.

814
00:47:55,420 --> 00:47:57,081
Do we have time
for a card trick?
Yes.

815
00:47:57,155 --> 00:47:58,850
I believe we have eternity.

816
00:47:58,923 --> 00:48:01,289
I'm going to show you
a little trick now.

817
00:48:01,759 --> 00:48:04,523
I just want to say
from the bottom of my heart,
I mean this sincerely...

818
00:48:05,196 --> 00:48:06,561
I say this
with all due respect.

819
00:48:06,631 --> 00:48:09,293
You are a wonderful group and
a fantastic group of people.

820
00:48:09,367 --> 00:48:12,029
I love you and I feel that
coming back from you.

821
00:48:12,103 --> 00:48:16,437
And you may be deceased,
but you should not
be discouraged.

822
00:48:16,507 --> 00:48:17,838
Because, you know...

823
00:48:17,909 --> 00:48:20,469
Don't think of being dead
as a handicap.

824
00:48:20,545 --> 00:48:22,672
You know,
when I was a child,
I stuttered.

825
00:48:22,747 --> 00:48:25,147
But with stick-to-it-iveness
and perseverance,

826
00:48:25,216 --> 00:48:27,183
you know, you can never tell
what could happen.

827
00:48:27,251 --> 00:48:28,684
Now, I want you
to take a card, Alma.

828
00:48:28,752 --> 00:48:30,014
Go ahead,
take any card you want.

829
00:48:30,087 --> 00:48:31,782
Just pick it. Pick it.
Go ahead, sweetheart.

